{"name":"Introduction to Episode 1","permission":{"default":0,"nxWKrSSCtrgMV99N":3},"flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":0,"handout-archived":false}},"content":"\n<section class=\"secret\"><p>GM Notes : </p><h2>Episode 1: Greenest In Flames</h2>The town of Greenest was founded by the halfling Dharva Scatterheart, a rogue who fancied herself the queen of the Greenfields. Scatterheart passed away without ever achieving that level of eminence, but her town grew into a thriving community. Its success isn't surprising, since Greenest is the only town of any size astride the Uldoon Trail, the most direct road between the eastern cities of the Dragon Coast, Cormyr, and Sembia with the Coast Way running south to the great cities of Amn, Tethyr, and far Calimshan. The trade caravans that pass through Greenest bring gold to the town's merchants and craftsfolk, and Governor Nighthill runs the town at the behest of the inhabitants.<br><br>The adventurers might be on the road from one town to another or returning to their homes after a trip away. Alternatively, they could be accompanying a merchant or wealthy traveler as bodyguards. Many restless young people of Faerûn have had their first taste of travel and adventure as caravan guards.<br><br>You can adapt <em>Tyranny of Dragons</em> to different regions of the Realms or to a different setting with a bit more preparation on your part. Change the names and locations to suit your campaign<br><hr><h3>Character Hooks</h3>To tie the characters' backstories to the <em>Tyranny of Dragons</em> campaign more closely, see <a class=\"entity-link\" data-entity=JournalEntry data-id=MDNmM2FkZTQ5ZmQ3 ><i class=\"fas fa-book-open\"></i>Hoard of the Dragon Queen Character Background Options</a>.<br></section>","img":"worlds/hoard-of-the-dragon-queen/journal/001_-_Episode_1_3A_Greenest_in_Flames/000_-_Introduction_to_Episode_1/avatar.png","_id":"C1Z6JH081RTSq1uI"}
