{"_id":"M2E3Y2I2MmYxM2U2","name":"Roll20 Note About Battle Map Scale","permission":{"default":0},"folder":null,"flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":1,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":10000,"entryTime":0,"content":"\n<section class=\"secret\"><p>GM Notes : </p>Map scale varies across the collection of battle maps within <em>Hoard of the Dragon Queen</em>. To make movement and token placement ideal, we have adjusted the grid on some of the maps so that tokens are easier to select and manipulate. Listed below are all the maps in this module and what scale they are currently set at. <br><hr><h3>Non-Scaled Maps</h3>These maps do not have a grid and provide no scaling information.<br><br><strong>Non-Scaled Maps in <em>Hoard of the Dragon Queen</em></strong><br><ul><li>The Sword Coast</li></ul><br><strong>Roll20 Note:</strong> A rough scale has been approximated for The Sword Coast map by drawing upon other compliant sources.<br> <hr><h3>Non-Gridded Maps</h3>These maps do not have a grid, but are sized so that if you use the <strong>Measurement Tool</strong>, it will count the correct distance length.<br><br><strong>Non-Gridded Maps<strong> in <em>Hoard of the Dragon Queen</em></strong></strong><br><ul><li>Greenest</li><li>Raider Camp</li></ul><hr><h3></h3><h3>20 Foot Maps</h3>Each grid square on the art is 20' with further subdivisions in the Roll20 grid (<strong>Grid Size</strong> set to <strong>0.5</strong> units and <strong>Map Scale</strong> set to <strong>10</strong> feet). Each Roll20 grid square is 5'. Tokens are sized accordingly to <em>Dungeons and Dragons</em> Rules (5', 10', 15', 20'). No adjustments are needed for strategy accuracy.<br><br><strong>20 Foot Maps in </strong><i style=\"font-weight: bold\">Hoard of the Dragon Queen </i><br><ul><li>Ground Floor - Castle Naerytar</li><li>Second Floor - Castle Naerytar</li><li>Third Floor - Castle Naerytar</li></ul><hr><h3>10 Foot Maps</h3>Each grid square on the art is 10' with a single subdivision in the Roll20 grid (<strong>Grid Size</strong> set to <strong>0.5</strong> units). Each Roll20 grid square is 5'. Tokens are sized accordingly to <em>Dungeons and Dragons</em> Rules (5', 10', 15', 20'). No adjustments are needed for strategy accuracy.<br><br><strong>10 Foot Maps in </strong><i style=\"font-weight: bold\">Hoard of the Dragon Queen </i><br><ul><li>Dungeon - Castle Naerytar</li><li>Parnast</li></ul><hr><h3>5 Foot Maps</h3>Each grid square is 5' on the art as well as 5' on the Roll20 grid. No adjustments are needed.<br><br><strong>5</strong><strong> Foot Maps in <em><i style=\"font-weight: bold\">Hoard of the Dragon Queen </i></em></strong><br><ul><li>Dragon Hatchery</li><li>Carnath Roadhouse</li><li>Ground Floor - Hunting Lodge</li><li>Upper Floor - Hunting Lodge</li><li>Lower Courtyard - Skyreach Castle</li><li>Upper Courtyard - Skyreach Castle</li><li>Ice Tunnels - Skyreach Castle</li><li>All Random Battlemaps</li></ul></section>","img":""}
{"name":"Arrow-Catching Shield","permission":{"default":0,"nxWKrSSCtrgMV99N":3},"flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":1,"handout-archived":false}},"content":"<h4>Arrow-Catching Shield</h4><em>Armor (shield), rare (requires attunement)</em><br><br>\tYou gain a +2 bonus to AC against ranged attacks while you wield this shield. This bonus is in addition to the shield's normal bonus to AC. In addition, whenever an attacker makes a ranged attack against a target within 5 feet of you, you can use your reaction to become the target of the attack instead.<br><br>","img":"","_id":"M4eveHvkWOrRHBwD"}
