{"_id":"NzIyNzgxNDQ0ZThi","name":"Roll20 Note: Game Settings","permission":{"default":0},"folder":null,"flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":4,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":40000,"entryTime":0,"content":"This module has been set up with the following Game Settings. For more information on how to change these settings, please check out the <a href=\"https://wiki.roll20.net/Game_Settings_Page\">Game Settings Wiki.</a><br><br><h3>Token Settings</h3><strong>Bar 1:</strong> HP<br><strong>Bar 2:</strong> NPC AC<br><strong>Bar 3:</strong> Intentionally left blank for GM use<br><strong>Show Nameplate Toggle:</strong> On<br><br><strong>Light Radius:</strong> Used for Darkvision or if a NPC exudes light<br><strong>All Players See Light:</strong> On if NPC exudes light<br><strong>Has Sight Toggle:</strong> Off, for performance. <br><h3><br>Sheet Settings</h3><strong>Roll Queries:</strong> Always Roll Advantage<br><strong>Whisper Rolls to GM:</strong> Always Whisper Rolls<br><strong>Auto Roll Damage:</strong> Auto Roll Damage and Crit<br>","img":""}
{"name":"Handout: Gray Ooze","permission":{"default":0,"nxWKrSSCtrgMV99N":3},"flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":9,"handout-archived":false}},"content":"","img":"worlds/hoard-of-the-dragon-queen/journal/013_-_Player_Handouts/000_-_Creatures__26_Monsters/009_-_Handout_3A_Gray_Ooze/avatar.png","_id":"O43bIG61SH9n4G67"}
{"_id":"OGY0M2Q3NjBiMmM0","name":"Roll20 Note about NPC Initiative","permission":{"default":0},"folder":null,"flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":2,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":20000,"entryTime":0,"content":"\n<section class=\"secret\"><p>GM Notes : </p>Like PCs, the D&amp;D 5th Edition NPC Sheet allows you to roll NPC Initiative directly from it. For NPCs, just click on the d20 icon at the top of their statblock on their sheet and it'll roll for Initiative.<br><br>If you have the <a href=\"https://wiki.roll20.net/Turn_Tracker\">Turn Tracker</a> tool open, having the NPC token selected while rolling Initiative will automatically add the NPC and its initiative roll to the tracker. Creatures on the GM layer that are added to the tracker in this fashion will have their entries hidden from the players.<br><br>You can also create a global <a href=\"https://wiki.roll20.net/Macros\">Macro</a> that will pop up as a Token Action button in the upper left hand corner of the tabletop every time a token is selected. This will allow you to roll without looking at the NPC sheet at all. The macro formula should look just like this:<br><pre style=\"font-size: 11.7px\">%{selected|npc_init}</pre></section>","img":""}
{"_id":"OGY5OGQyNTkxYWQx","name":"Roll20 Note: Module Shortcuts","permission":{"default":0},"folder":null,"flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":5,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":50000,"entryTime":0,"content":"The Roll20 Tabletop is equipped with keyboard shortcuts. Some of the most popular are listed below. <a href=\"https://wiki.roll20.net/Keyboard_Shortcuts\">A full list of shortcuts can be found on the wiki.</a><br><br><strong>Double click:</strong> Opens Token options, including light radius and \"Has Sight\" options.<br><strong>Shift+ Double click:</strong> Opens up token's character sheet<br><br><strong>Ctrl/Cmd+Shift+O:</strong> Move selected object to token layer<br><strong>Ctrl/Cmd+Shift+K:</strong> Move selected object to GM layer<br><br><strong>Pressing \"Z\" with an object selected</strong> shows a larger version of that object in a modal popup<br><strong>Pressing Shift+Z as the GM</strong> shows all players the larger version of that object<br><strong>Pressing Ctrl/Cmd+L with a token selected</strong> <strong>as the GM</strong> to view the environment as that token would<br>","img":""}
